Adult.description: Eurasian Tree Sparrows, which live around St. Louis, Missouri, in the United States have an entirely rufous crown and a dark spot on the cheek unlike the grayish-cheeked House Sparrow.

Female.description: The female Dickcissel has a longer, heavier bill than a female House Sparrow. It also has a yellow eyebrow that the House Sparrow does not have.

Adult.description: Black-throated Sparrows have a white eyebrow and mustache stripe not seen on House Sparrows.

Nonbreeding adult.description: Harris's Sparrows have a plain brown face, without the male House Sparrow's white cheeks and chestnut neck.

Immature.description: Juvenile White-crowned Sparrows have reddish-brown crowns and thin white wingbars, whereas female House Sparrows have a pale brown crown without distinct wingbars.

Female/immature.description: Female House Finches have heavily streaked underparts and lack the female House Sparrow's broad buffy eyebrow stripe.
